I can feel it.

469
00:22:09.940 --> 00:22:11.372
- Okay.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(RUMBLING)</font>

470
00:22:11.374 --> 00:22:14.475
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(BOTH GASP)</font>
- Oh. no. What now?

471
00:22:14.477 --> 00:22:16.245
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> The Trolls?

472
00:22:16.247 --> 00:22:19.149
- Kristoff! We missed you!
- Oh!

473
00:22:19.884 --> 00:22:21.083
Pabbie.

474
00:22:21.085 --> 00:22:24.119
Well. never a dull moment
with you two.

475
00:22:24.121 --> 00:22:27.155
I hope you're prepared
for what you have done. Elsa.

476
00:22:27.157 --> 00:22:31.026
Angry magical spirits are not
for the faint of heart.

477
00:22:31.028 --> 00:22:32.861
Why are they still angry?

478
00:22:32.863 --> 00:22:35.297
What does all of this
have to do with Arendelle?

479
00:22:35.299 --> 00:22:37.101
Let me see what I can see.

480
00:22:39.770 --> 00:22:43.574
The past is not what it seems.

481
00:22:44.407 --> 00:22:47.242
A wrong demands to be righted.

482
00:22:47.244 --> 00:22:50.279
- Arendelle is not safe.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA GASPS)</font>

483
00:22:50.281 --> 00:22:53.849
The truth must be found.

484
00:22:53.851 --> 00:22:54.952
Without it...

485
00:22:56.287 --> 00:22:58.454
I see no future.

486
00:22:59.089 --> 00:23:00.555
No future?

487
00:23:00.557 --> 00:23:02.824
When one can see no future...

488
00:23:02.826 --> 00:23:06.995
all one can do
is the next right thing.

489
00:23:06.997 --> 00:23:08.964
The next right thing

490
00:23:08.966 --> 00:23:10.899
is for me to go
to the Enchanted Forest...

491
00:23:10.901 --> 00:23:12.533
and find that voice.

492
00:23:12.535 --> 00:23:13.735
Kristoff. can I borrow
your wagon

493
00:23:13.737 --> 00:23:14.903
- and Sven?
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">SVEN:</font> Hmm?

494
00:23:14.905 --> 00:23:16.504
I'm not very comfortable
with the idea of that.

495
00:23:16.506 --> 00:23:18.740
- You are not going alone.
- Anna. no.

496
00:23:18.742 --> 00:23:21.442
I have my powers
to protect me. You don't.

497
00:23:21.444 --> 00:23:23.145
Excuse me.
I climbed the North Mountain...

498
00:23:23.147 --> 00:23:24.313
survived a frozen heart.

499
00:23:24.315 --> 00:23:25.380
and saved you
from my ex-boyfriend...

500
00:23:25.382 --> 00:23:26.715
and I did it all without powers.

501
00:23:26.717 --> 00:23:28.317
- so. you know. I'm coming.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(INHALES)</font>

502
00:23:28.319 --> 00:23:29.651
Me. too. I'll drive.

503
00:23:29.653 --> 00:23:31.353
I'll bring the snacks!

504
00:23:31.355 --> 00:23:33.422
I will look after your people.

505
00:23:33.424 --> 00:23:34.522
Please make sure they stay

506
00:23:34.524 --> 00:23:36.158
out of the kingdom
until we return.

507
00:23:36.160 --> 00:23:37.659
Of course.

508
00:23:37.661 --> 00:23:39.294
Let's let them know.

509
00:23:39.296 --> 00:23:42.230
Anna. I am worried for her.

510
00:23:42.232 --> 00:23:43.632
We have always feared

511
00:23:43.634 --> 00:23:46.401
Elsa's powers were too much
for this world.

512
00:23:46.403 --> 00:23:49.940
Now. we must pray
they are enough.

513
00:23:50.506 --> 00:23:51.640
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(BREATHES SHARPLY)</font>

514
00:23:51.642 --> 00:23:53.811
I won't let anything
happen to her.

515
00:23:54.278 --> 00:23:55.813
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> Hyah!

516
00:23:59.249 --> 00:24:01.149
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> Who's into trivia?

517
00:24:01.151 --> 00:24:02.718
I am. Okay.

518
00:24:02.720 --> 00:24:05.387
Did you know that water
has memory? True fact.

519
00:24:05.389 --> 00:24:07.589
It's disputed by many.
but it's true.

520
00:24:07.591 --> 00:24:08.890
Did you know men are six times

521
00:24:08.892 --> 00:24:10.592
more likely to be
struck by lightning?

522
00:24:10.594 --> 00:24:12.794
Did you know gorillas
burp when they're happy?

523
00:24:12.796 --> 00:24:15.397
Did you know we blink
four million times a day?

524
00:24:15.399 --> 00:24:17.366
Did you know
wombats poop squares?

525
00:24:17.368 --> 00:24:18.667
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> Did you know
sleeping quietly

526
00:24:18.669 --> 00:24:20.501
on long journeys
prevents insanity?

527
00:24:20.503 --> 00:24:21.870
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF CACKLING)</font>

528
00:24:21.872 --> 00:24:23.372
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> Yeah. that's not true.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> It is.

529
00:24:23.374 --> 00:24:24.573
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> It's true.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ELSA:</font> Definitely true.

530
00:24:24.575 --> 00:24:26.008
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> No. it's the truth.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN MOANS)</font>

531
00:24:26.010 --> 00:24:27.642
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> Well.
that was unanimous.

532
00:24:27.644 --> 00:24:29.711
But I will look it up
when we get home.

533
00:24:29.713 --> 00:24:32.114
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF SNORING AND MUMBLING)</font>

534
00:24:32.116 --> 00:24:33.915
They're both asleep.

535
00:24:33.917 --> 00:24:36.987
So. what do you wanna do?

536
00:24:37.988 --> 00:24:39.021
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHUCKLES)</font>

537
00:24:39.023 --> 00:24:42.157
Sven. keep us steady. will ya?

538
00:24:42.159 --> 00:24:43.892
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN GRUNTS)</font>

539
00:24:43.894 --> 00:24:45.694
- Hmm...
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(VOICE CRACKS)</font> Anna. Ahem.

540
00:24:45.696 --> 00:24:46.828
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(IN NORMAL VOICE)</font> Anna?
- Mm-hmm?

541
00:24:46.830 --> 00:24:48.697
Remember
our first trip like this...

542
00:24:48.699 --> 00:24:50.832
when I said
you'd have to be crazy

543
00:24:50.834 --> 00:24:52.634
to want to marry
a man you just met?

544
00:24:52.636 --> 00:24:54.269
Wait. what? Crazy?

545
00:24:54.271 --> 00:24:57.039
You didn't say I was crazy.
You think I'm crazy?

546
00:24:57.041 --> 00:24:58.607
No. I did.

547
00:24:58.609 --> 00:25:00.442
- You were...
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">SVEN:</font> Huh? {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

548
00:25:00.444 --> 00:25:01.643
...not crazy.

549
00:25:01.645 --> 00:25:03.078
Clearly. {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHUCKLES)</font>

550
00:25:03.080 --> 00:25:04.713
Just naive.

551
00:25:04.715 --> 00:25:08.216
Not naive. Just. uh. new to love.
Like I was.

552
00:25:08.218 --> 00:25:12.821
And when you're new.
you're bound to get it wrong.

553
00:25:12.823 --> 00:25:14.856
So you're saying
I'm wrong for you.

554
00:25:14.858 --> 00:25:16.925
What? No. no.
I'm not saying

555
00:25:16.927 --> 00:25:19.528
- you're wrong. or crazy.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(THE VOICE VOCALIZING)</font>

556
00:25:19.530 --> 00:25:21.763
- Kristoff. stop. Please.
- Good idea.

557
00:25:21.765 --> 00:25:23.465
I hear it.
I hear the voice.

558
00:25:23.467 --> 00:25:25.434
You do?

559
00:25:25.436 --> 00:25:28.603
- Olaf. wake up.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF GRUNTS)</font>

560
00:25:28.605 --> 00:25:30.607
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN MOANS)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA GASPS SOFTLY)</font>

561
00:25:31.241 --> 00:25:33.343
- Whoa.
- Wow.

562
00:25:57.501 --> 00:25:59.534
Whoa! What the...

563
00:25:59.536 --> 00:26:00.771
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS. LAUGHS)</font>

564
00:26:01.872 --> 00:26:02.938
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

565
00:26:02.940 --> 00:26:04.039
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(LAUGHS)</font>

566
00:26:04.041 --> 00:26:05.776
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHOOPS. LAUGHS)</font>

567
00:26:06.510 --> 00:26:08.245
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF GRUNTS. LAUGHS)</font>

568
00:26:18.355 --> 00:26:19.890
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> Whoa.

569
00:26:26.830 --> 00:26:29.698
Promise me.
we do this together. okay?

570
00:26:29.700 --> 00:26:31.201
I promise.

571
00:26:40.410 --> 00:26:41.977
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN GROANS)</font>
- It's okay.

572
00:26:41.979 --> 00:26:44.346
Did you know
that an enchanted forest

573
00:26:44.348 --> 00:26:45.947
is a place of transformation?

574
00:26:45.949 --> 00:26:47.883
I have no idea
what that means...

575
00:26:47.885 --> 00:26:49.751
but I can't wait to see

576
00:26:49.753 --> 00:26:53.556
what it's gonna do
to each one of us.

577
00:26:53.558 --> 00:26:54.656
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHOOSHING)</font>

578
00:26:54.658 --> 00:26:56.057
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ELSA:</font> Hey!
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> What is this?

579
00:26:56.059 --> 00:26:57.560
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> No pushing.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> Stop it.

580
00:26:57.562 --> 00:26:58.896
- Whoa. whoa. whoa!
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ELSA:</font> It's too fast.

581
00:26:59.463 --> 00:27:00.695
What was that?

582
00:27:00.697 --> 00:27:02.632
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF LAUGHING)</font>

583
00:27:02.634 --> 00:27:04.366
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> No. No. no. no.

584
00:27:04.368 --> 00:27:06.301
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(BOTH GASP)</font>

585
00:27:06.303 --> 00:27:07.903
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> And we're locked in.

586
00:27:07.905 --> 00:27:10.038
Probably should have seen
that one coming.

587
00:27:10.040 --> 00:27:11.706
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF LAUGHING)</font>

588
00:27:11.708 --> 00:27:14.244
This forest is beautiful.

589
00:27:15.045 --> 00:27:16.211
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> Ooh.

590
00:27:16.213 --> 00:27:18.382
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING AND TWITTERING IN DISTANCE)</font>

591
00:27:29.526 --> 00:27:30.827
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(MOANS)</font>

592
00:27:39.903 --> 00:27:43.673
The dam. It still stands.

593
00:27:43.675 --> 00:27:46.508
It was
in Grand Pabbie's visions.

594
00:27:46.510 --> 00:27:48.009
But why?

595
00:27:48.011 --> 00:27:50.845
I don't know. but it's still
in good shape. Thank goodness.

596
00:27:50.847 --> 00:27:51.947
What do you mean?

597
00:27:51.949 --> 00:27:53.148
Well. if that dam broke...

598
00:27:53.150 --> 00:27:55.183
it would send
a tidal wave so big

599
00:27:55.185 --> 00:27:57.752
it would wash away
everything on this fjord.

600
00:27:57.754 --> 00:27:59.154
Everything?

601
00:27:59.156 --> 00:28:01.691
But Arendelle's on this fjord.

602
00:28:01.693 --> 00:28:03.825
Nothing's gonna happen
to Arendelle. Anna.

603
00:28:03.827 --> 00:28:05.327
It's gonna be fine.

604
00:28:05.329 --> 00:28:07.195
Come here.
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SIGHS)</font>

605
00:28:07.197 --> 00:28:08.832
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN SNORTS)</font>

606
00:28:09.199 --> 00:28:11.099
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SNORTING)</font>

607
00:28:11.101 --> 00:28:12.568
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS SOFTLY)</font>

608
00:28:12.570 --> 00:28:15.270
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CLEARS THROAT)</font> You know.
under different circumstances.

609
00:28:15.272 --> 00:28:18.740
this would be a. uh.
pretty romantic place.

610
00:28:18.742 --> 00:28:19.808
Don't you think?

611
00:28:19.810 --> 00:28:20.875
Different circumstances?

612
00:28:20.877 --> 00:28:22.277
You mean.
like with someone else?

613
00:28:22.279 --> 00:28:23.912
What? No! No.

614
00:28:23.914 --> 00:28:25.280
I'm saying...
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

615
00:28:25.282 --> 00:28:26.682
Just in case we don't
make it out of here...

616
00:28:26.684 --> 00:28:27.882
Wait. what?

617
00:28:27.884 --> 00:28:29.284
You don't think we're gonna
make it out of here?

618
00:28:29.286 --> 00:28:30.620
No. No!

619
00:28:30.622 --> 00:28:32.153
I mean. no.
we will make it out of here.

620
00:28:32.155 --> 00:28:33.656
Well. technically the odds
are kind of complicated.

621
00:28:33.658 --> 00:28:35.257
- but my point is...
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GROANS)</font>

622
00:28:35.259 --> 00:28:36.491
In case we die...

623
00:28:36.493 --> 00:28:38.893
- You think we're gonna die?
- No! No. no. no.

624
00:28:38.895 --> 00:28:40.161
- Where's Elsa?
- We will die at some point.

625
00:28:40.163 --> 00:28:41.296
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> I swore that
I wouldn't leave her side.

626
00:28:41.298 --> 00:28:42.732
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> Not in any
recent time will we die.

627
00:28:42.734 --> 00:28:44.232
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> Elsa!
- But way far in the future.

628
00:28:44.234 --> 00:28:45.533
we will die.

629
00:28:45.535 --> 00:28:46.803
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

630
00:28:48.305 --> 00:28:49.404
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN MOANS)</font>

631
00:28:49.406 --> 00:28:51.508
- Don't patronize me.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN SNORTS)</font>

632
00:28:53.678 --> 00:28:55.546
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>

633
00:28:56.513 --> 00:28:58.048
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(RUSTLING)</font>

634
00:29:00.317 --> 00:29:01.617
Elsa!

635
00:29:01.619 --> 00:29:02.951
There you are.

636
00:29:02.953 --> 00:29:05.220
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

637
00:29:05.222 --> 00:29:06.890
Okay. good.

638
00:29:07.324 --> 00:29:09.026
Where's Olaf?

639
00:29:09.259 --> 00:29:10.425
Um...

640
00:29:10.427 --> 00:29:11.495
Anna?

641
00:29:12.062 --> 00:29:13.428
Elsa?

642
00:29:13.430 --> 00:29:14.965
Sven?

643
00:29:15.399 --> 00:29:17.100
Samantha?

644
00:29:17.568 --> 00:29:19.467
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHEEZING LAUGH)</font>

645
00:29:19.469 --> 00:29:22.504
I don't even know a Samantha.

646
00:29:22.506 --> 00:29:23.938
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY)</font>

647
00:29:23.940 --> 00:29:25.507
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WIND WHISTLING)</font>

648
00:29:25.509 --> 00:29:26.577
Whoa!

649
00:29:29.246 --> 00:29:30.247
Mm.

650
00:29:31.214 --> 00:29:32.349
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>

651
00:29:33.216 --> 00:29:34.552
That's normal.

652
00:29:35.753 --> 00:29:36.987
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

653
00:29:40.824 --> 00:29:42.492
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>

654
00:29:46.897 --> 00:29:49.197
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>
- What was that?

655
00:29:49.199 --> 00:29:50.231
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>

656
00:29:50.233 --> 00:29:51.234
Samantha?

657
00:29:52.469 --> 00:29:54.271
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

658
00:29:56.206 --> 00:30:00.342
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> This will all make
sense when I am older </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

659
00:30:00.344 --> 00:30:04.346
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Someday I will see
that this makes sense </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

660
00:30:04.348 --> 00:30:08.183
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> One day when I'm old and wise
I'll think back and realize </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

661
00:30:08.185 --> 00:30:11.754
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> That these were all
completely normal events! </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

662
00:30:11.756 --> 00:30:13.090
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(YELPS)</font>

663
00:30:14.224 --> 00:30:18.026
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> I'll have all the answers
when I'm older </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

664
00:30:18.028 --> 00:30:22.330
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Like why
we're in this dark enchanted wood </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

665
00:30:22.332 --> 00:30:24.432
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> I know in a couple years </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

666
00:30:24.434 --> 00:30:26.434
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> These will seem like childish fears </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

667
00:30:26.436 --> 00:30:29.572
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> And so I know this isn't bad.
it's good </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

668
00:30:29.574 --> 00:30:30.974
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Excuse me </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

669
00:30:31.743 --> 00:30:35.778
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Growing up means adapting </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

670
00:30:35.780 --> 00:30:39.314
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Puzzling out your
world and your place </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

671
00:30:39.316 --> 00:30:43.652
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> When I'm more mature
I'll feel totally secure </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

672
00:30:43.654 --> 00:30:47.889
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Being watched by something
with a creepy. creepy face </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

673
00:30:47.891 --> 00:30:49.324
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WATER BUBBLING)</font>

674
00:30:49.326 --> 00:30:51.128
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SCREAMING)</font>

675
00:30:56.500 --> 00:30:58.400
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(EAGLE SCREAMS)</font>

676
00:30:58.402 --> 00:31:03.037
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> See. that will all make
sense when I am older </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

677
00:31:03.039 --> 00:31:06.243
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> So there's no need to
be terrified or tense </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

678
00:31:07.745 --> 00:31:10.813
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> I'll just dream
about a time </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

679
00:31:10.815 --> 00:31:14.683
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> When I'm in my aged prime </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

680
00:31:14.685 --> 00:31:17.118
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> 'Cause when you're older </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

681
00:31:17.120 --> 00:31:22.591
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Absolutely everything makes sense!  </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

682
00:31:22.593 --> 00:31:23.960
This is fine.

683
00:31:25.763 --> 00:31:27.730
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> Whoa!
- Olaf!

684
00:31:27.732 --> 00:31:29.464
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF CACKLING)</font>

685
00:31:29.466 --> 00:31:30.967
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL YELP)</font>

686
00:31:32.469 --> 00:31:33.669
Hey. guys.

687
00:31:33.671 --> 00:31:35.571
Meet the Wind Spirit.

688
00:31:35.573 --> 00:31:37.172
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL YELPING)</font>

689
00:31:37.174 --> 00:31:39.073
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> Coming through!

690
00:31:39.075 --> 00:31:40.442
Ooh. I think I'm gonna be sick.

691
00:31:40.444 --> 00:31:43.579
I'd hold your hair back.
but I can't find my arms.

692
00:31:43.581 --> 00:31:45.415
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN BELLOWS)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(YELPING)</font>

693
00:31:47.451 --> 00:31:48.452
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>

694
00:31:50.487 --> 00:31:51.554
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>

695
00:31:51.556 --> 00:31:53.421
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>
- Hey! Stop!

696
00:31:53.423 --> 00:31:54.989
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL WHIMPERING)</font>

697
00:31:54.991 --> 00:31:57.060
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(KRISTOFF SCREAMING)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF LAUGHING)</font>

698
00:32:02.733 --> 00:32:04.067
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF GRUNTS)</font>

699
00:32:05.368 --> 00:32:06.369
Elsa!

700
00:32:06.737 --> 00:32:08.071
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTING)</font>

701
00:32:09.506 --> 00:32:11.241
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> Let her go!

702
00:32:13.845 --> 00:32:15.243
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(STRAINING)</font>

703
00:32:15.245 --> 00:32:17.013
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> Anna.
be careful!

704
00:32:17.582 --> 00:32:19.249
That's my sister!

705
00:32:19.684 --> 00:32:21.218
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(LAUGHTER)</font>

706
00:32:23.554 --> 00:32:25.453
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">MATTIAS:</font> Prince Agnarr!

707
00:32:25.455 --> 00:32:28.158
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WEAPONS CLANGING)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

708
00:32:28.659 --> 00:32:29.991
For Arendelle.

709
00:32:29.993 --> 00:32:31.394
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SWORD SWISHES)</font>

710
00:32:32.763 --> 00:32:33.896
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">FIGHTER:</font> Look out!

711
00:32:33.898 --> 00:32:35.230
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(RUNEARD SCREAMS)</font>

712
00:32:35.232 --> 00:32:36.667
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">YOUNG AGNARR:</font> Father!
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA GRUNTS)</font>

713
00:32:42.038 --> 00:32:43.406
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(BOTH PANT)</font>

714
00:32:44.407 --> 00:32:45.774
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(PANTING)</font>

715
00:32:45.776 --> 00:32:48.109
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

716
00:32:48.111 --> 00:32:49.177
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN SNIFFS)</font>

717
00:32:49.179 --> 00:32:51.780
- What are these?
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN MOANS)</font>

718
00:32:51.782 --> 00:32:55.818
Oh. they look like
moments in time.

719
00:32:55.820 --> 00:32:57.686
What's that thing you say. Olaf?

720
00:32:57.688 --> 00:32:59.153
The thing... Oh!

721
00:32:59.155 --> 00:33:01.155
My theory about
advancing technologies

722
00:33:01.157 --> 00:33:02.558
as both our savior and our doom?

723
00:33:02.560 --> 00:33:05.026
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(STAMMERS)</font> No. not that one.
The one about...

724
00:33:05.028 --> 00:33:06.261
- The one about cucumbers?
- No.

725
00:33:06.263 --> 00:33:07.328
The thing about water.

726
00:33:07.330 --> 00:33:09.965
Oh! Yeah.
Water has memory.

727
00:33:09.967 --> 00:33:11.533
The water that
makes up you and me

728
00:33:11.535 --> 00:33:13.769
has passed through
at least four humans...

729
00:33:13.771 --> 00:33:15.706
and/or animals before us.

730
00:33:16.641 --> 00:33:17.940
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> Hmm.

731
00:33:17.942 --> 00:33:20.543
And remembers everything.

732
00:33:20.545 --> 00:33:21.509
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN GRUNTING)</font>

733
00:33:21.511 --> 00:33:23.746
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHUCKLES)</font>
The wind's back.

734
00:33:23.748 --> 00:33:25.981
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(EXCLAIMS)</font> Delicious.

735
00:33:25.983 --> 00:33:28.786
I think I'll name you Gale.

736
00:33:29.486 --> 00:33:30.553
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(EXCLAIMS)</font>

737
00:33:30.555 --> 00:33:32.955
- Get out of there. Whoa!
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>

738
00:33:32.957 --> 00:33:35.089
- Oh. Hi.
- Aren't you curious?

739
00:33:35.091 --> 00:33:36.659
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA CHUCKLES)</font>

740
00:33:36.661 --> 00:33:38.829
- You in a better mood now?
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ANNA GIGGLES)</font>

741
00:33:43.400 --> 00:33:44.434
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ANNA GASPS)</font>

742
00:33:48.940 --> 00:33:52.309
Father.
That's Father.

743
00:33:54.045 --> 00:33:55.644
This girl.

744
00:33:55.646 --> 00:33:57.780
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> She's saving him.

745
00:33:57.782 --> 00:33:59.180
She's Northuldra.

746
00:33:59.182 --> 00:34:01.617
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(HIGH-PITCHED CHITTERING)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL GASP)</font>

747
00:34:01.619 --> 00:34:02.985
What is that?

748
00:34:02.987 --> 00:34:04.789
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ELSA:</font> Olaf. get behind me.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHIMPERS)</font>

749
00:34:07.324 --> 00:34:08.757
What are you gonna do with that?

750
00:34:08.759 --> 00:34:10.059
I have no idea.

751
00:34:10.061 --> 00:34:12.095
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING CONTINUES)</font>

752
00:34:19.971 --> 00:34:21.606
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ANNA GRUNTS)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL GASP)</font>

753
00:34:22.740 --> 00:34:23.806
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN GRUNTS)</font>

754
00:34:23.808 --> 00:34:25.540
Lower your weapon.

755
00:34:25.542 --> 00:34:28.176
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WEAPONS CLANG)</font>
- And you lower yours.

756
00:34:28.178 --> 00:34:30.311
Arendellian soldiers?

757
00:34:30.313 --> 00:34:32.246
Threatening my people.
Lieutenant?

758
00:34:32.248 --> 00:34:35.050
Invading my dance space. Yelena?

759
00:34:35.052 --> 00:34:36.217
Why does that soldier
look so familiar?

760
00:34:36.219 --> 00:34:37.620
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> No. no. no.

761
00:34:37.622 --> 00:34:38.687
Lieutenant!

762
00:34:38.689 --> 00:34:39.755
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">MATTIAS:</font> Get the sword!

763
00:34:39.757 --> 00:34:41.358
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)</font>

764
00:34:42.593 --> 00:34:43.859
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL GRUNTING)</font>

765
00:34:43.861 --> 00:34:45.663
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL YELP AND GRUNT)</font>

766
00:34:47.598 --> 00:34:49.197
That was magic.

767
00:34:49.199 --> 00:34:50.699
Did you see that?

768
00:34:50.701 --> 00:34:52.868
Of course I saw it.

769
00:34:52.870 --> 00:34:54.502
You chose a nice. cold greeting.

770
00:34:54.504 --> 00:34:56.337
They've been trapped in
here this whole time?

771
00:34:56.339 --> 00:34:58.007
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> Yeah.
- What do we do now?

772
00:34:58.009 --> 00:34:59.209
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> I got this.

773
00:34:59.644 --> 00:35:01.076
Hi. I'm Olaf.

774
00:35:01.078 --> 00:35:02.711
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(MAN GASPS)</font>

775
00:35:02.713 --> 00:35:05.881
Oh. sorry. Yeah. I just
find clothes restricting.

776
00:35:05.883 --> 00:35:08.117
Bet you're wondering who
we are and why we're here.

777
00:35:08.119 --> 00:35:09.985
It's really quite simple.

778
00:35:09.987 --> 00:35:12.286
It began with two sisters.

779
00:35:12.288 --> 00:35:14.155
One born with magical powers.

780
00:35:14.157 --> 00:35:15.557
One born powerless.

781
00:35:15.559 --> 00:35:17.492
Their love of snowmen. infinite.

782
00:35:17.494 --> 00:35:19.160
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS YOUNG ELSA)</font>
Anna. no! Too high!

783
00:35:19.162 --> 00:35:20.395
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(IN NORMAL VOICE)</font>
Blast! {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GROANS)</font>

784
00:35:20.397 --> 00:35:22.131
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS YOUNG ELSA)</font>
Mama! Papa! Help!

785
00:35:22.133 --> 00:35:24.265
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(IN NORMAL VOICE)</font> Slam!
Doors shutting everywhere.

786
00:35:24.267 --> 00:35:26.334
Sisters torn apart.

787
00:35:26.336 --> 00:35:28.436
Well. at least
they have their parents.

788
00:35:28.438 --> 00:35:30.304
Their parents are dead.

789
00:35:30.306 --> 00:35:32.240
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS ANNA)</font> Oh.
Oh. hi. I'm Anna.

790
00:35:32.242 --> 00:35:33.575
I'll marry a man I just met.

791
00:35:33.577 --> 00:35:35.044
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(IN NORMAL VOICE)</font>
Elsa's gonna blow!

792
00:35:35.046 --> 00:35:37.412
Snow! Snow! Aah. run!

793
00:35:37.414 --> 00:35:39.648
Magic pulses
through my snowflakes.

794
00:35:39.650 --> 00:35:41.215
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font> I live.

795
00:35:41.217 --> 00:35:43.986
Ice palace for one.
Ice palace for one.

796
00:35:43.988 --> 00:35:45.721
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS ELSA)</font> Get out. Anna.
Pew! Pew!

797
00:35:45.723 --> 00:35:47.856
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS ANNA)</font> My heart.
- Oh. my goodness.

798
00:35:47.858 --> 00:35:49.692
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS PABBIE)</font> Only an act
of true love can save you.

799
00:35:49.694 --> 00:35:51.729
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS HANS)</font> Here's
a true love's kiss.

800
00:35:52.395 --> 00:35:53.862
You're not worth it.

801
00:35:53.864 --> 00:35:55.496
Guess what?
I'm the bad guy.

802
00:35:55.498 --> 00:35:56.932
What?

803
00:35:56.934 --> 00:36:00.102
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(IN NORMAL VOICE)</font> And Anna
freezes to death forever.

804
00:36:00.104 --> 00:36:01.772
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(EXHALES)</font>
- Oh. Anna.

805
00:36:02.372 --> 00:36:03.706
Then she unfreezes!

806
00:36:03.708 --> 00:36:05.406
Oh. and then Elsa woke up
the magical spirits...

807
00:36:05.408 --> 00:36:06.875
and we were forced
out of our kingdom.

808
00:36:06.877 --> 00:36:08.443
Now our only hope is to find
the truth about the past...

809
00:36:08.445 --> 00:36:09.912
but we don't have a clue
how to do that...

810
00:36:09.914 --> 00:36:11.279
except Elsa's hearing voices.

811
00:36:11.281 --> 00:36:12.781
- so we got that going for us.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA SIGHS)</font>

812
00:36:12.783 --> 00:36:14.317
Any questions?

813
00:36:17.054 --> 00:36:18.723
I think they got it.

814
00:36:20.223 --> 00:36:22.091
Are you really
Queen of Arendelle?

815
00:36:22.093 --> 00:36:23.257
I am.

816
00:36:23.259 --> 00:36:24.425
Why would nature reward

817
00:36:24.427 --> 00:36:26.394
a person of Arendelle
with magic?

818
00:36:26.396 --> 00:36:28.764
Perhaps to make up for the
actions of your people.

819
00:36:28.766 --> 00:36:30.465
My people are innocent.

820
00:36:30.467 --> 00:36:32.500
We would have never
attacked first.

821
00:36:32.502 --> 00:36:34.069
May the truth be found.

822
00:36:34.071 --> 00:36:36.237
- Mm...
- Hi. I'm sorry.

823
00:36:36.239 --> 00:36:38.073
- Uh. what's happening?
- Hmm.

824
00:36:38.075 --> 00:36:40.241
That's it.
Lieutenant Mattias!

825
00:36:40.243 --> 00:36:42.077
Library. second portrait
on the left.

826
00:36:42.079 --> 00:36:44.447
You were our father's
official guard.

827
00:36:44.849 --> 00:36:46.615
Agnarr.

828
00:36:46.617 --> 00:36:48.516
What did happen to your parents?

829
00:36:48.518 --> 00:36:51.787
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SIGHS)</font> Our parents' ship went
down in the Southern Sea...

830
00:36:51.789 --> 00:36:52.890
six years ago.

831
00:36:54.658 --> 00:36:55.726
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SIGHS)</font>

832
00:36:57.595 --> 00:37:00.829
I see him.
I see him in your faces.

833
00:37:00.831 --> 00:37:01.897
Really?

834
00:37:01.899 --> 00:37:03.364
Soldiers.

835
00:37:03.366 --> 00:37:06.367
We may be getting on in years.
but we're still strong.

836
00:37:06.369 --> 00:37:08.706
And proud to serve Arendelle.

837
00:37:09.907 --> 00:37:11.907
Wait. Please.

838
00:37:11.909 --> 00:37:13.976
Someone has called me here.

839
00:37:13.978 --> 00:37:16.111
If I can just find them...

840
00:37:16.113 --> 00:37:17.345
I believe they have the answers

841
00:37:17.347 --> 00:37:20.281
that may help us
free this forest.

842
00:37:20.283 --> 00:37:22.517
Trust me. I just want to help.

843
00:37:22.519 --> 00:37:25.020
We only trust nature.

844
00:37:25.022 --> 00:37:26.757
When nature speaks...

845
00:37:28.225 --> 00:37:29.323
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL GASP)</font>

846
00:37:29.325 --> 00:37:30.525
...we listen.

847
00:37:30.527 --> 00:37:32.895
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font> This will all
make sense when I'm older.

848
00:37:32.897 --> 00:37:33.898
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHIMPERS)</font>

849
00:37:34.397 --> 00:37:35.831
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">MAN:</font> Fire Spirit!

850
00:37:35.833 --> 00:37:37.398
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL CLAMORING)</font>

851
00:37:37.400 --> 00:37:38.934
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">YELENA:</font> Get back. everyone!

852
00:37:38.936 --> 00:37:40.805
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">MATTIAS:</font> Head for the river!

853
00:37:50.714 --> 00:37:53.081
No! No! No! The reindeer!
That's a dead end!

854
00:37:53.083 --> 00:37:54.084
Come on. Sven!

855
00:37:54.752 --> 00:37:56.053
We'll get them.

856
00:37:56.887 --> 00:37:58.354
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(PANICKED SHOUTING)</font>

857
00:37:58.956 --> 00:38:00.891
Elsa! Get out of there!

858
00:38:01.859 --> 00:38:02.860
No. no. no.

859
00:38:05.830 --> 00:38:07.064
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTING)</font>

860
00:38:07.798 --> 00:38:09.097
Elsa!

861
00:38:09.099 --> 00:38:10.500
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(COUGHING)</font>

862
00:38:16.106 --> 00:38:17.471
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN BELLOWS)</font>

863
00:38:17.473 --> 00:38:18.876
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(REINDEERS BELLOW)</font>

864
00:38:20.476 --> 00:38:22.947
Come on. buddy.
we can do this. Hyah!

865
00:38:25.149 --> 00:38:26.750
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(COUGHING)</font>

866
00:38:27.818 --> 00:38:28.917
Anna!

867
00:38:28.919 --> 00:38:30.087
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(PANTING)</font>

868
00:38:33.824 --> 00:38:35.224
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ANNA:</font> Oh!

869
00:38:35.226 --> 00:38:36.390
Get her out of here.

870
00:38:36.392 --> 00:38:38.762
No! Elsa!

871
00:39:00.584 --> 00:39:02.518
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CROAKING)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA GASPS)</font>

872
00:39:12.395 --> 00:39:13.896
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GROWLS)</font>

873
00:39:13.898 --> 00:39:15.032
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

874
00:39:16.066 --> 00:39:17.668
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS QUIZZICALLY)</font>

875
00:39:20.871 --> 00:39:22.172
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>

876
00:39:30.114 --> 00:39:31.246
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SIZZLES)</font>

877
00:39:31.248 --> 00:39:32.650
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA WINCING)</font>

878
00:39:36.353 --> 00:39:37.821
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SIZZLING)</font>

879
00:39:43.360 --> 00:39:44.662
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHUCKLES)</font>

880
00:39:48.399 --> 00:39:49.667
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHUCKLES)</font>

881
00:39:52.736 --> 00:39:55.070
They're all looking at us.
aren't they?

882
00:39:55.072 --> 00:39:56.073
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERS)</font>

883
00:39:56.907 --> 00:39:58.175
Got any advice?

884
00:39:58.742 --> 00:39:59.743
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

885
00:40:00.077 --> 00:40:02.244
Nothing?

886
00:40:02.246 --> 00:40:04.579
Hmm. Should I know
what that means?

887
00:40:04.581 --> 00:40:06.684
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(THE VOICE VOCALIZING)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SQUEAKS)</font>

888
00:40:07.184 --> 00:40:09.551
You hear it. too.

889
00:40:09.553 --> 00:40:11.620
Somebody's calling us.

890
00:40:11.622 --> 00:40:14.423
Who is it?
What do we do?

891
00:40:14.425 --> 00:40:15.626
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CROAKS)</font>

892
00:40:18.128 --> 00:40:19.529
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS SOFTLY)</font>

893
00:40:20.297 --> 00:40:21.632
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>

894
00:40:22.498 --> 00:40:24.868
Okay. keep going north.

895
00:40:27.705 --> 00:40:28.670
Elsa!

896
00:40:28.672 --> 00:40:29.905
- Oh. thank goodness!
- Anna.

897
00:40:29.907 --> 00:40:32.040
- Are you okay?
- What were you doing?

898
00:40:32.042 --> 00:40:33.141
You could've been killed.

899
00:40:33.143 --> 00:40:35.310
You can't just follow me
into fire.

900
00:40:35.312 --> 00:40:37.511
You don't want me
to follow you into fire.

901
00:40:37.513 --> 00:40:40.514
then don't run into fire.

902
00:40:40.516 --> 00:40:43.554
You're not being careful. Elsa.

903
00:40:44.088 --> 00:40:45.387
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SIGHS)</font>

904
00:40:45.389 --> 00:40:48.390
I'm sorry.
Are you okay?

905
00:40:48.392 --> 00:40:50.392
I've been better.

906
00:40:50.394 --> 00:40:53.564
Hmm. I know
what you need.

907
00:40:55.132 --> 00:40:56.732
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(PEOPLE GASP)</font>

908
00:40:56.734 --> 00:40:58.602
Where did you get that scarf?

909
00:40:59.370 --> 00:41:01.336
That's a Northuldra scarf.

910
00:41:01.338 --> 00:41:02.503
What?

911
00:41:02.505 --> 00:41:05.440
This is from one of
our oldest families.

912
00:41:05.442 --> 00:41:07.209
It was our mother's.

913
00:41:07.211 --> 00:41:08.278
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA GASPS)</font>

914
00:41:16.053 --> 00:41:17.486
Elsa.

915
00:41:17.488 --> 00:41:18.887
I see it.

916
00:41:18.889 --> 00:41:21.023
It's Mother.

917
00:41:21.025 --> 00:41:24.294
Mother saved
Father's life that day.

918
00:41:28.298 --> 00:41:30.699
Our mother was Northuldra.

919
00:41:30.701 --> 00:41:32.200
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL GASP AND MURMUR)</font>

920
00:41:32.202 --> 00:41:33.270
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF GASPS)</font>

921
00:41:34.304 --> 00:41:36.106
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERING)</font>

922
00:41:42.312 --> 00:41:44.314
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(EXCLAIMS)</font>

923
00:41:46.950 --> 00:41:48.018
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>

924
00:41:52.589 --> 00:41:54.792
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHANTING YOIK)</font>

925
00:41:58.429 --> 00:41:59.763
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(BOTH GASP)</font>

926
00:42:01.265 --> 00:42:03.100
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL HARMONIZING)</font>

927
00:42:14.945 --> 00:42:16.313
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF JOINS IN)</font>

928
00:42:19.116 --> 00:42:21.218
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHANTING CONTINUES)</font>

929
00:42:31.595 --> 00:42:33.862
We are called Northuldra.

930
00:42:33.864 --> 00:42:37.034
We are the people of the sun.

931
00:42:39.136 --> 00:42:42.704
I promise you I will
free this forest...

932
00:42:42.706 --> 00:42:44.208
and restore Arendelle.

933
00:42:45.476 --> 00:42:47.543
That's a pretty
big promise. Elsa.

934
00:42:47.545 --> 00:42:49.044
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(EXCITED CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)</font>

935
00:42:49.046 --> 00:42:51.982
Free the Forest?
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHUCKLES)</font> Wow.

936
00:42:52.416 --> 00:42:53.549
I'm sorry.

937
00:42:53.551 --> 00:42:55.317
It's just. uh. some of us
were born in here.

938
00:42:55.319 --> 00:42:57.452
we've never even seen
a clear sky.

939
00:42:57.454 --> 00:42:58.653
I get it.

940
00:42:58.655 --> 00:43:00.622
- The name's Ryder.
- Kristoff.

941
00:43:00.624 --> 00:43:02.190
I heard the voice again.

942
00:43:02.192 --> 00:43:03.658
We need to go north.

943
00:43:03.660 --> 00:43:06.094
But the Earth Giants now
roam the north at night.

944
00:43:06.096 --> 00:43:08.296
You can leave in the morning.

945
00:43:08.298 --> 00:43:09.464
I'm Honeymaren.

946
00:43:09.466 --> 00:43:11.869
Honeymaren. we'll do all we can.

947
00:43:13.237 --> 00:43:15.370
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHILDREN GIGGLING)</font>

948
00:43:15.372 --> 00:43:16.738
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">OLAF:</font> Hey. let me ask you.

949
00:43:16.740 --> 00:43:17.906
How do you guys cope...

950
00:43:17.908 --> 00:43:20.041
with the ever-increasing
complexity of thought

951
00:43:20.043 --> 00:43:22.346
- that comes with maturity?
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(KID GRUNTS)</font>

952
00:43:23.213 --> 00:43:24.813
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GIGGLES)</font>
- Brilliant!

953
00:43:24.815 --> 00:43:26.148
- Oh!
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(LAUGHS)</font>

954
00:43:26.150 --> 00:43:28.316
It's so refreshing to talk
to the youth of today.

955
00:43:28.318 --> 00:43:29.718
Our future's in bright hands.

956
00:43:29.720 --> 00:43:31.052
Oh. no. no.
Don't chew that.

957
00:43:31.054 --> 00:43:32.954
You don't know
what I've stepped in.

958
00:43:32.956 --> 00:43:34.789
I can't seem
to get her attention.

959
00:43:34.791 --> 00:43:36.424
Or even say the right thing.

960
00:43:36.426 --> 00:43:37.893
Well. you're in luck.

961
00:43:37.895 --> 00:43:39.995
I know nothing about women.

962
00:43:39.997 --> 00:43:41.096
But I do know that we have

963
00:43:41.098 --> 00:43:44.099
the most amazing way
of proposing.

964
00:43:44.101 --> 00:43:45.167
If we start now.

965
00:43:45.169 --> 00:43:46.434
- we'll be ready by dawn.
- Really?

966
00:43:46.436 --> 00:43:47.637
Best part.

967
00:43:47.639 --> 00:43:49.171
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHISPERS)</font> it involves
a lot of reindeer.

968
00:43:49.173 --> 00:43:51.306
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">KRISTOFF:</font> Whoa.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SVEN GRUNTS)</font>

969
00:43:51.308 --> 00:43:52.507
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">MATTIAS:</font> Hey.
back at home...

970
00:43:52.509 --> 00:43:54.409
Halima still over
at Hudson's Hearth?

971
00:43:54.411 --> 00:43:55.477
She is.

972
00:43:55.479 --> 00:43:57.245
Really?
She married?

973
00:43:57.247 --> 00:43:58.380
Mm-mm.

974
00:43:58.382 --> 00:44:01.551
Oh. wow. Why didn't that
make me feel better?

975
00:44:01.553 --> 00:44:03.253
What else do you miss?

976
00:44:04.087 --> 00:44:05.655
My father.

977
00:44:05.657 --> 00:44:07.691
He passed long before all this.

978
00:44:08.825 --> 00:44:11.493
He was a great man.

979
00:44:11.495 --> 00:44:13.028
Built us a good life
in Arendelle.

980
00:44:13.030 --> 00:44:15.997
But taught me to never take
the good for granted.

981
00:44:15.999 --> 00:44:18.366
He'd say. "Be prepared.

982
00:44:18.368 --> 00:44:19.968
"Just when you think
you've found your way.

983
00:44:19.970 --> 00:44:23.305
"life will throw you
onto a new path."

984
00:44:23.307 --> 00:44:25.407
What do you do when it does?

985
00:44:25.409 --> 00:44:26.841
Don't give up.

986
00:44:26.843 --> 00:44:30.412
Take it one step
at a time and...

987
00:44:30.414 --> 00:44:33.215
Just do the next right thing?

988
00:44:33.217 --> 00:44:34.684
Yeah.

989
00:44:34.686 --> 00:44:35.919
- You got it.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GIGGLES)</font>

990
00:44:39.022 --> 00:44:42.290
I wanna show you
something. May I?

991
00:44:42.292 --> 00:44:43.460
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(WHIMPERS SOFTLY)</font>

992
00:44:44.928 --> 00:44:47.563
You know air. fire.
water. and earth.

993
00:44:47.565 --> 00:44:48.897
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">ELSA:</font> Yes.

994
00:44:48.899 --> 00:44:50.465
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#ca6500">HONEYMAREN:</font> But. look.
there's a fifth spirit...

995
00:44:50.467 --> 00:44:54.169
said to be a bridge between
us and the magic of nature.

996
00:44:54.171 --> 00:44:55.470
A fifth spirit?

997
00:44:55.472 --> 00:44:56.738
Some say

998
00:44:56.740 --> 00:44:59.507
they heard it call out
the day the Forest fell.

999
00:44:59.509 --> 00:45:01.176
My father heard it.

1000
00:45:01.178 --> 00:45:03.613
Do you think
that is who's calling me?

1001
00:45:03.615 --> 00:45:08.183
Maybe. Alas.
only Ahtohallan knows.

1002
00:45:08.185 --> 00:45:09.886
Ahtohallan.

1003
00:45:11.355 --> 00:45:15.824
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> Dive down deep into her sound </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

1004
00:45:15.826 --> 00:45:20.295
{\fscx83\fscy83\fad(250.250)}<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font><font color="#FFFF00"> But not too far or you'll be drowned  </font><font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

1005
00:45:20.297 --> 00:45:22.197
Why do lullabies
always have to have

1006
00:45:22.199 --> 00:45:23.898
some terrible warning in them?

1007
00:45:23.900 --> 00:45:25.834
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHUCKLES)</font> I wonder
that all the time.

1008
00:45:25.836 --> 00:45:28.370
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)</font>

1009
00:45:28.372 --> 00:45:30.171
Earth Giants.

1010
00:45:30.173 --> 00:45:32.075
What are they doing down here?

1011
00:45:33.010 --> 00:45:34.511
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ALL WHIMPER)</font>
- Shh!

1012
00:45:35.045 --> 00:45:36.079
Hide.

1013
00:45:36.780 --> 00:45:38.415
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(PANTS)</font>

1014
00:45:39.283 --> 00:45:41.084
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)</font>

1015
00:45:41.785 --> 00:45:43.487
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(OLAF GASPS)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERS)</font>

1016
00:45:44.388 --> 00:45:45.487
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SHUSHING)</font>

1017
00:45:45.489 --> 00:45:47.289
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font> They're coming!

1018
00:45:47.291 --> 00:45:48.559
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(BLOWING)</font>

1019
00:45:49.526 --> 00:45:51.293
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(YELPS. EXHALING)</font>

1020
00:45:51.295 --> 00:45:52.462
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPING)</font>

1021
00:45:53.797 --> 00:45:55.598
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(SIGHS)</font>

1022
00:45:55.600 --> 00:45:58.101
This is why
we don't play with fire.

1023
00:45:59.236 --> 00:46:02.705
Oh. I can't stay mad at you.
Why are you so cute?

1024
00:46:02.707 --> 00:46:04.740
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(FOOTSTEPS CONTINUE THUDDING)</font>

1025
00:46:04.742 --> 00:46:05.942
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>

1026
00:46:13.884 --> 00:46:16.086
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GRUNTS)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ELSA PANTING)</font>

1027
00:46:24.261 --> 00:46:25.395
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS SOFTLY)</font>

1028
00:46:26.463 --> 00:46:28.363
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(ANNA SCOFFS)</font>

1029
00:46:28.365 --> 00:46:32.033
Please tell me you were not
about to follow them.

1030
00:46:32.035 --> 00:46:34.269
What if I can settle them
like I did the wind and fire?

1031
00:46:34.271 --> 00:46:36.037
Or what if they can crush you

1032
00:46:36.039 --> 00:46:38.273
before you even get the chance?

1033
00:46:38.275 --> 00:46:41.943
Remember. the goal
is to find the voice...

1034
00:46:41.945 --> 00:46:44.946
find the truth. and get us home.

1035
00:46:44.948 --> 00:46:47.182
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(PANTING)</font> Hey. guys.
That was close.

1036
00:46:47.184 --> 00:46:48.483
- I know.
- {\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(CHITTERS)</font>

1037
00:46:48.485 --> 00:46:50.985
The giants sensed me.
They may come back here.

1038
00:46:50.987 --> 00:46:53.488
I don't want to put anyone
at risk again.

1039
00:46:53.490 --> 00:46:54.824
And you're right. Anna.

1040
00:46:54.826 --> 00:46:56.792
We've got to find the voice.

1041
00:46:56.794 --> 00:46:57.992
We're going now.

1042
00:46:57.994 --> 00:46:59.527
Okay. We're going.

1043
00:46:59.529 --> 00:47:00.929
Let me just...

1044
00:47:00.931 --> 00:47:03.031
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

1045
00:47:03.033 --> 00:47:05.601
Wait. Where are
Kristoff and Sven?

1046
00:47:05.603 --> 00:47:08.370
Oh. yeah. I think they
took off with that Ryder guy

1047
00:47:08.372 --> 00:47:09.605
and a bunch of reindeer.

1048
00:47:09.607 --> 00:47:10.905
- They left?
- Mm-hmm.

1049
00:47:10.907 --> 00:47:13.541
Just left
without saying anything?

1050
00:47:13.543 --> 00:47:15.580
Who knows the ways of men?

1051
00:47:16.146 --> 00:47:17.147
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(GASPS)</font>

1052
00:47:22.787 --> 00:47:25.554
Am I supposed to feel
this ridiculous?

1053
00:47:25.556 --> 00:47:26.990
Oh. yeah. Definitely.

1054
00:47:27.692 --> 00:47:28.791
Everyone ready?

1055
00:47:28.793 --> 00:47:29.924
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS REINDEER 1)</font> Ready!

1056
00:47:29.926 --> 00:47:31.126
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS REINDEER 2)</font> Uh.
I could use a rehearsal.

1057
00:47:31.128 --> 00:47:32.193
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(AS REINDEER 3)</font>
I love love.

1058
00:47:32.195 --> 00:47:34.129
Wait. You talk
for them. too?

1059
00:47:34.131 --> 00:47:35.564
{\fad(250.250)}<font color="#00abfd">(IN NORMAL VOICE)</font>
I do.

1060
00:47:35.566 --> 00:47:37.132
It's like you can actually
hear what they're thinking.

1061
00:47:37.134 --> 00:47:39.602
Yeah. And then
you just say it.

1062
00:47:39.604 --> 00:47:41.169
And then you just say it.

1063
00:47:41.171 --> 00:47:42.372
